  "local_port": 33950,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the some of the best lines in English songs?",
  "response": "Here\u2019s a curated selection of iconic and impactful lines from English songs, spanning genres, eras, and themes. These lines resonate for their poetic depth, cultural influence, or emotional power:\n\n---\n\n### **Timeless & Poetic**  \n1. **\"Imagine all the people living life in peace.\"**  \n   \u2014 John Lennon (\"Imagine\")  \n   *A utopian anthem for unity and hope.*  \n\n2. **\"The answer, my friend, is blowin\u2019 in the wind.\"**  \n   \u2014 Bob Dylan (\"Blowin\u2019 in the Wind\")  \n   *A haunting reflection on societal change.*  \n\n3. **\"There\u2019s a crack in everything, that\u2019s how the light gets in.\"**  \n   \u2014 Leonard Cohen (\"Anthem\")  \n   *A metaphor for finding beauty in imperfection.*  \n\n4. **\"Hello darkness, my old friend.\"**  \n   \u2014 Simon & Garfunkel (\"The Sound of Silence\")  \n   *A melancholic ode to introspection.*  \n\n---\n\n### **Defiant & Empowering**  \n5. **\"You can\u2019t always get what you want, but if you try sometimes, you get what you need.\"**  \n   \u2014 The Rolling Stones (\"You Can\u2019t Always Get What You Want\")  \n   *A life lesson in resilience and perspective.*  \n\n6. **\"I will survive!\"**  \n   \u2014 Gloria Gaynor (\"I Will Survive\")  \n   *The ultimate breakup empowerment anthem.*  \n\n7. **\"What doesn\u2019t kill you makes you stronger.\"**  \n   \u2014 Kelly Clarkson (\"Stronger\")  \n   *A rallying cry for overcoming adversity.*  \n\n---\n\n### **Cinematic & Dramatic**  \n8. **\"Is this the real life? Is this just fantasy?\"**  \n   \u2014 Queen (\"Bohemian Rhapsody\")  \n   *A surreal opening to a rock opera masterpiece.*  \n\n9. **\"It\u2019s a hard knock life for us!\"**  \n   \u2014 *Annie* (\"It\u2019s a Hard Knock Life\")  \n   *A gritty, catchy lament from the musical.*  \n\n---\n\n### **Modern & Reflective**  \n10. **\"I\u2019m the problem, it\u2019s me.\"**  \n    \u2014 Taylor Swift (\"Anti-Hero\")  \n    *A candid admission of self-doubt.*  \n\n11. **\"When the party\u2019s over, I\u2019ll still be loyal.\"**  \n    \u2014 Billie Eilish (\"when the party\u2019s over\")  \n    *A haunting take on emotional exhaustion.*  \n\n12. **\"You\u2019re gonna hear me roar.\"**  \n    \u2014 Katy Perry (\"Roar\")  \n    *A bold declaration of self-empowerment.*  \n\n---\n\n### **Hip-Hop & Cultural Impact**  \n13. **\"Spread love, it\u2019s the Brooklyn way.\"**  \n    \u2014 The Notorious B.I.G. (\"Juicy\")  \n    *A nod to community and positivity.*  \n\n14. **\"You better lose yourself in the music, the moment.\"**  \n    \u2014 Eminem (\"Lose Yourself\")  \n    *A motivational call to seize opportunity.*  \n\n---\n\n### **Romantic & Heartfelt**  \n15. **\"All you need is love.\"**  \n    \u2014 The Beatles (\"All You Need Is Love\")  \n    *A simple yet universal truth.*  \n\n16. **\"Every breath you take, every move you make, I\u2019ll be watching you.\"**  \n    \u2014 The Police (\"Every Breath You Take\")  \n    *Often mistaken for romance, it\u2019s a chilling ode to obsession.*  \n\n---\n\n### **Social Commentary**  \n17. **\"Don\u2019t it always seem to go that you don\u2019t know what you\u2019ve got till it\u2019s gone?\"**  \n    \u2014 Joni Mitchell (\"Big Yellow Taxi\")  \n    *A lament for environmental and personal loss.*  \n\n18. **\"Fight the power!\"**  \n    \u2014 Public Enemy (\"Fight the Power\")  \n    *A revolutionary call to challenge systemic injustice.*  \n\n---\n\nThese lines endure because they capture universal emotions, challenge norms, or paint vivid stories. Music\u2019s beauty lies in its subjectivity\u2014what moves one person might differ for another. What\u2019s your favorite? \ud83c\udfb6",
